It’s no surprise that Vitamin C is a superstar skincare ingredient. ​

This multi-utility ingredient brings out the best for almost everyone when used correctly. ​

The stability of this ingredient is however a concern, because exposure to air, heat and light may slowly degrade the vitamin​

How to apply: ​

Take 2-3 drops of vitamin C serum on your palms, rub it together and dab it on your face. Massage it on your face evenly, then wait for 15 – 20 minutes to apply moisturiser. ​

You’re ready to glow ;)

#IngredientFocus CALENDULA EXTRACT - A plant-based ingredient your skin didn't know it needed​​

Derived from family of daisies known as asteraceae, calendula is known for its anti - inflammatory & moisturising properties since ages.​​

If you are facing skin concerns such as eczema, rosacea, skin irritation, the anti-inflammatory properties of calendula helps soothe skin.​

For acne prone skin, you can consider using calendula with other acne fighting ingredients such as salicylic acid & benzoyl peroxide.​​

The fatty acids in calendula extract increases skin's ability to retain moisture & absorb all the nutrients to keep it hydrated and nourished. ​

The list doesn't end here, the flavonoids in Calendula helps protect skin against external aggressors such as dirt, pollution & free radicals which could lead to premature aging of the skin.​​

Calendula extract is available in various types of products such as oils, moisturizers, lip balms, serums and more​​

Some products that contain Calendula as a star ingredient: Clineral PSO body shampoo, Aziclear Serum, Clineral X-ZEM Hand Cream, Shangpree Gold Hydrogel Eye Mask to name a few.​

Speak to our expert who would be happy to guide you if this is something you should look to add to your skincare regime. You can shop for the products from our e-store @agelessxpress ​

Fractional Lasers aren’t one-size-fits-all — especially not for Indian skin.✨️

With higher levels of pigment cells (melanin), Indian skin tends to be more reactive to heat, friction, and trauma — often leading to pigmentation, scarring, or prolonged healing. That’s why treatment selection should always prioritize safety, precision, and long-term skin health.
